103 SECTION 6.
104 Code Section 19-7-1 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to in whom parental
105 power lies, how such power lost, and recovery for homicide of a child or unborn child, is
106 amended by revising paragraph (1) of subsection (c) as follows:
107 "(c)(1) In every case of the homicide of a child, minor or sui juris, there shall be some
108 party entitled to recover the full value of the life of the child, either as provided in this
109 Code section or as provided in Chapter 4 of Title 51. For the homicide of an unborn
110 child, the right to recover for the full value of the life of such child shall begin at the point
111 at which a detectable human heartbeat, as such term is defined in Code Section 1-2-1, is
112 present fertilization."
113 SECTION 7.
114 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
